# Arena Web — env vars
#
# Copy to .env.local and fill in. Commit .env.example, never .env.local.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required: Supabase access (same project as nexus-web)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used to read the active human's auth_id from the shared nx_session cookie
# and to read/write the arena_connections table.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL="https://your-project.supabase.co"
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY="..."

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required in production: Arena's own shared secret
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Eve uses this in the Authorization: Bearer <secret> header when calling
# Arena's executor endpoints. Same value must be set on nexus-web.
ARENA_SECRET="generate-a-strong-secret-for-prod"

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional: per-provider credentials
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When unset, the corresponding executor falls back to mock mode and tags
# the audit log entry with `mocked: true`. Eve still works; nothing actually
# happens in the real world.

# ClickUp: personal API token from https://app.clickup.com/settings/apps
CLICKUP_API_KEY=""
# Default list to drop tasks into when Eve doesn't specify one
CLICKUP_LIST_ID=""

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cookie domain — for cross-subdomain auth share
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# In prod set to ".talkcircles.io" (or whatever registrable domain hosts both
# nexus-web and arena-web) so the nx_session cookie set by nexus-web is
# readable by arena-web. Leave unset in dev — same-origin cookies work fine.
SESSION_COOKIE_DOMAIN=""
